# Public Parks backend — environment template.
#
# Copy to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in values for local development.
# All variables follow NamingConventions.md §8: upper SNAKE_CASE with an approved
# service-area prefix. The config layer at startup validates every value via Zod
# and refuses to boot on missing/malformed input.
#
# === SECRETS POLICY (see DECISIONS.md → "Secrets management") =================
# - Never put real secret values in this file. This file documents the SHAPE of
#   the environment; it is committed to the repo. Real values go in `.env`
#   locally (gitignored) and in the deployment platform's secret store for
#   staging/production.
# - Never write secrets into source code, Docker images, log lines, or
#   committed config. Pino redaction (observability decision) covers logs.
# - Every secret has a `SECRET_REGISTRY` entry in `src/config/env.schema.ts`
#   pairing it with known dev placeholder values; startup refuses to boot in
#   staging/production if any registered secret still holds a placeholder.
# - Rotate every secret before launch and on any suspected compromise.
#   Per-environment credentials are required — no cross-environment reuse.
#
# === ENVIRONMENT SEPARATION (see DECISIONS.md → "Environment separation") ====
# - `development`, `staging`, `production`, and `test` are fully isolated.
#   Separate Postgres, Redis, object storage, queue namespaces, Telebirr
#   credentials, JWT signing keys, and admin accounts per environment.
# - Connection strings have a `DEV_INFRA_REGISTRY` entry in env.schema.ts that
#   matches `localhost` / `127.0.0.1` / `host.docker.internal` patterns;
#   startup refuses to boot in staging/production if any registered URL still
#   points at dev infrastructure.
# - Production data is never copied into staging/development without project-
#   owner approval logged in DECISIONS.md AND PII/payment-data masking.
# =============================================================================

# --- APP ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Application environment. One of: development | staging | production | test.
APP_NODE_ENV=development

# HTTP port the API listens on.
APP_PORT=3000

# --- LOG ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pino log level. One of: fatal | error | warn | info | debug | trace.
LOG_LEVEL=info

# --- DB -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Primary Postgres connection string. Must include the PostGIS extension (see
# DECISIONS.md → "PostgreSQL + PostGIS provisioning"). Use postgres:// or
# postgresql:// scheme. The value below matches the docker-compose stack at
# `./docker-compose.yml` for local dev — do not reuse it for staging/prod.
DB_PRIMARY_URL=postgres://parks:parks_dev@localhost:5432/parks_dev
